column5: CEI I am thinking being Schott stated clearly they completed the due diligence and final documents have been submitted it could be the final audit by the exchange on financials holding it up and the Series C holder talking advantage of the hold up time to try get their best deal in this transaction Being that Schott said final documents have been submitted to the exchange I have to assume a purchase agreement has been reached settled and on completion of satisfactory compliance with the exchanges review it should by now be a binding agreement pending settlement with the series C holder of which I think maybe int he process of final review by the exchange at this stage Normal time frame a closing as such ranges between 8 to 10 weeks with audit of financials settlement of purchase agreements and final approval by the exchange Being they had received preliminary approval of the terms of the transaction as set forth in the nonbinding term sheet between the parties 042219
